[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capability": "BLS",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "latitude": 38.9100,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "longitude": -77.0450,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "status": "AVAILABLE",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "zone": "ZONE-A",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "shift_start": "2026-06-01T18:00:00Z",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "calls_today": 1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "unit_id": "BLS-4",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capability": "BLS",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "latitude": 38.9300,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "longitude": -77.0100,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "status": "AVAILABLE",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "zone": "ZONE-D",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "shift_start": "2026-06-01T18:00:00Z",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "calls_today": 2,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return fleet
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def get_available_units(fleet, required_capability="BLS"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Filter fleet to units that are available and meet the capability requirement.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ALS units can handle both ALS and BLS calls (paramedics can do everything
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     EMTs can do, plus more). BLS units can only handle BLS calls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     available = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for unit in fleet:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if unit["status"] != "AVAILABLE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # ALS units satisfy any capability requirement.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # BLS units only satisfy BLS requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         unit_level = CAPABILITY_LEVELS[unit["capability"]]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         required_level = CAPABILITY_LEVELS[required_capability]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if unit_level >= required_level:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             available.append(unit)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return available
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Travel Time Estimation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The main recipe uses Amazon Location Service for real road-network travel times with traffic. Here we use the Haversine formula with a speed estimate as a stand-in. In production, you'd call Location Service's CalculateRouteMatrix API and cache results in ElastiCache.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def haversine_distance_km(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Calculate straight-line distance between two GPS coordinates in kilometers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the "as the crow flies" distance. Real road distance is typically
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1.3x to 1.6x longer in urban areas (the "circuity factor").
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     R = 6371  # Earth's radius in km
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dlat = math.radians(lat2 - lat1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dlon = math.radians(lon2 - lon1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     a = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         math.sin(dlat / 2) ** 2
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         + math.cos(math.radians(lat1))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         * math.cos(math.radians(lat2))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         * math.sin(dlon / 2) ** 2
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     c = 2 * math.atan2(math.sqrt(a), math.sqrt(1 - a))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return R * c
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def estimate_travel_time_seconds(origin_lat, origin_lon, dest_lat, dest_lon,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                                   emergency=True):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Estimate travel time in seconds between two points.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, replace this with a call to Amazon Location Service:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         client.calculate_route(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             CalculatorName="ems-router",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             DeparturePosition=[origin_lon, origin_lat],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             DestinationPosition=[dest_lon, dest_lat],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             TravelMode="Car",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             DepartNow=True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The Location Service response includes DurationSeconds accounting for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     real-time traffic. You'd then apply an emergency vehicle multiplier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (typically 0.7x to 0.8x of civilian travel time for L&S response).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For this example, we use Haversine distance with a circuity factor
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and speed estimate. It's wrong, but it's wrong in a predictable way
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     that lets you see the optimization logic clearly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     straight_line_km = haversine_distance_km(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         origin_lat, origin_lon, dest_lat, dest_lon
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Urban circuity factor: roads aren't straight lines.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # 1.4 is typical for grid-pattern cities. Winding suburbs might be 1.6+.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     road_distance_km = straight_line_km * 1.4
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     speed_kmh = SPEED_EMERGENCY_KMH if emergency else SPEED_NORMAL_KMH
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     travel_time_hours = road_distance_km / speed_kmh
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     travel_time_seconds = travel_time_hours * 3600
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return travel_time_seconds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Dispatch Scoring
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `score_candidates`. This is the heart of the system: evaluating each available unit against a call and producing a ranked list. The scoring function balances response time against system-level concerns like coverage preservation and crew welfare.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def compute_coverage_impact(unit, fleet, demand_zones):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Estimate how much system coverage degrades if we dispatch this unit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The idea: if this unit is the only one covering its zone, removing it
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     creates a critical gap. If three other units can also cover that zone,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     removing this one barely matters.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns a score from 0.0 (no impact) to 1.0 (critical gap created).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     zone = unit["zone"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Count how many other available units can cover this zone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     other_units_in_zone = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for other in fleet:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if other["unit_id"] == unit["unit_id"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if other["status"] != "AVAILABLE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if other["zone"] == zone:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             other_units_in_zone += 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Also check adjacent units that could reach this zone within threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # (simplified: in production, use actual travel times to zone centroid)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     zone_centroid = demand_zones.get(zone, {}).get("centroid")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if zone_centroid:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for other in fleet:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if other["unit_id"] == unit["unit_id"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if other["status"] != "AVAILABLE":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if other["zone"] == zone:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue  # already counted
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             travel = estimate_travel_time_seconds(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 other["latitude"], other["longitude"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 zone_centroid[0], zone_centroid[1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 emergency=True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if travel <= COVERAGE_THRESHOLD_SECONDS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 other_units_in_zone += 0.5  # partial credit for adjacent coverage
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convert to impact score: fewer backup units = higher impact
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if other_units_in_zone >= 2:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return 0.1  # well-covered zone, minimal impact
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif other_units_in_zone >= 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return 0.4  # one backup, moderate concern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return 0.9  # no backup, critical gap if we send this unit
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def normalize_value(value, max_value):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Normalize a value to 0.0-1.0 range. Clamps at 1.0."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return min(value / max_value, 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def score_candidates(call, fleet, demand_zones):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Score all available, capable units for a given call.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         call: dict with location, priority, required_capability, nature_code
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         fleet: list of all unit dicts (current fleet state)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         demand_zones: dict of zone_id -> {centroid, demand_weight}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of candidate dicts sorted by score (ascending = best first).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Each candidate includes unit_id, travel_time, score, and coverage_impact.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     required_cap = call.get("required_capability", "BLS")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     available = get_available_units(fleet, required_cap)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not available:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning("No available units meet capability requirement: %s", required_cap)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Select weight profile based on call priority
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     weights = PRIORITY_1_WEIGHTS if call["priority"] == 1 else DISPATCH_WEIGHTS
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     now = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for unit in available:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Travel time from unit's current position to call location
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         travel_time = estimate_travel_time_seconds(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             unit["latitude"], unit["longitude"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             call["location"]["lat"], call["location"]["lng"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             emergency=True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Coverage impact: what happens to system coverage if we send this unit?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         coverage_impact = compute_coverage_impact(unit, fleet, demand_zones)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Fatigue: hours on shift. Slight penalty after 10 hours.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         shift_start = datetime.datetime.fromisoformat(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             unit["shift_start"].replace("Z", "+00:00")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         hours_on_shift = (now - shift_start).total_seconds() / 3600
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         fatigue_penalty = max(0.0, (hours_on_shift - 10) * 0.1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Workload: calls run today, normalized against a reasonable max
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         workload_score = normalize_value(unit["calls_today"], 10)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Composite score (lower is better)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             weights["response_time"] * normalize_value(travel_time, 1200)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             + weights["coverage_impact"] * coverage_impact
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             + weights["fatigue"] * normalize_value(fatigue_penalty, 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             + weights["workload"] * workload_score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         candidates.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "unit_id": unit["unit_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capability": unit["capability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "travel_time_seconds": round(travel_time),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "coverage_impact": round(coverage_impact, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "score": round(score, 4),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Sort by score ascending (best candidate first)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates.sort(key=lambda c: c["score"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return candidates
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Hospital Destination Selection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `select_hospital`. After the unit arrives on scene and assesses the patient, the system recommends the best destination hospital based on clinical needs, transport time, and current capacity.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def build_hospital_status():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Synthetic hospital status data. In production, this comes from hospital
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     systems via EventBridge (diversion status, ED census, bed availability)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and is stored in DynamoDB for fast lookup.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hospitals = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "hospital_id": "HOSP-GWU",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "name": "GW University Hospital",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "location": {"lat": 38.9007, "lng": -77.0508},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capabilities": ["cath_lab", "interventional_cardiology",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                              "level_1_trauma", "stroke_center"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "ed_capacity": 45,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "current_ed_census": 24,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "diversion_status": "OPEN",  # OPEN, CONDITIONAL, FULL_DIVERSION
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "hospital_id": "HOSP-MEDSTAR",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "name": "MedStar Washington Hospital Center",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "location": {"lat": 38.9296, "lng": -77.0164},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capabilities": ["cath_lab", "interventional_cardiology",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                              "level_1_trauma", "stroke_center", "burn_center"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "ed_capacity": 60,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "current_ed_census": 52,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "diversion_status": "CONDITIONAL",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "hospital_id": "HOSP-SIBLEY",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "name": "Sibley Memorial Hospital",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "location": {"lat": 38.9378, "lng": -77.1052},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capabilities": ["stroke_center", "general_surgery"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "ed_capacity": 30,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "current_ed_census": 12,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "diversion_status": "OPEN",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return hospitals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def select_hospital(patient_needs, unit_location, hospitals):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Recommend the best destination hospital for a patient.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_needs: dict with required_capabilities (list), acuity_level (1-5)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         unit_location: dict with lat, lng (ambulance's current position)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         hospitals: list of hospital status dicts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Best hospital dict with transport_time and score, or None if no
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         eligible hospital found (which would be a serious system failure
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         in a real deployment).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     eligible = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for hospital in hospitals:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Hard filter: must have all required capabilities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         has_all_caps = all(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cap in hospital["capabilities"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for cap in patient_needs["required_capabilities"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if not has_all_caps:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Hard filter: diversion status
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if hospital["diversion_status"] == "FULL_DIVERSION":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if (hospital["diversion_status"] == "CONDITIONAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 and patient_needs["acuity_level"] > 2):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Conditional diversion: only accepting critical patients (acuity 1-2)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Transport time from unit's current location to hospital
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         transport_seconds = estimate_travel_time_seconds(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             unit_location["lat"], unit_location["lng"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             hospital["location"]["lat"], hospital["location"]["lng"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             emergency=True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Capacity score: how full is the ED? (0.0 = empty, 1.0 = at capacity)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         capacity_ratio = hospital["current_ed_census"] / hospital["ed_capacity"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Composite destination score (lower is better)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         dest_score = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             0.50 * normalize_value(transport_seconds, 1800)  # transport time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             + 0.35 * capacity_ratio                           # ED crowding
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             + 0.15 * (0.0 if len(hospital["capabilities"]) > 3 else 0.3)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # slight preference for higher-capability hospitals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         eligible.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             **hospital,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "transport_time_seconds": round(transport_seconds),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "transport_time_minutes": round(transport_seconds / 60, 1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capacity_ratio": round(capacity_ratio, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "score": round(dest_score, 4),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not eligible:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.error("No eligible hospitals found for patient needs: %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                      patient_needs)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Sort by score ascending (best destination first)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     eligible.sort(key=lambda h: h["score"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return eligible[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Coverage Optimization (Repositioning)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `optimize_repositioning`. This is the background solver that runs every few minutes. It identifies coverage gaps (zones where no available unit can respond within the target time) and computes optimal unit repositioning moves to close those gaps. This is where OR-Tools earns its keep.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def build_demand_zones():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Define coverage zones with centroids and demand weights.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, these come from the demand forecast model (SageMaker endpoint)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     which predicts call probability per zone for the next 30 minutes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     zones = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ZONE-A": {"centroid": (38.9072, -77.0369), "demand_weight": 0.30},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ZONE-B": {"centroid": (38.9200, -77.0200), "demand_weight": 0.25},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ZONE-C": {"centroid": (38.8950, -77.0500), "demand_weight": 0.20},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ZONE-D": {"centroid": (38.9300, -77.0100), "demand_weight": 0.15},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ZONE-E": {"centroid": (38.8800, -77.0300), "demand_weight": 0.10},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return zones
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def identify_coverage_gaps(fleet, demand_zones):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Find zones where no available unit can respond within the coverage threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns a list of gap dicts: zone_id, centroid, best_current_time, demand_weight.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     These are the zones the repositioning optimizer needs to fix.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     available_units = [u for u in fleet if u["status"] == "AVAILABLE"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     gaps = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for zone_id, zone_info in demand_zones.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Skip very low demand zones (not worth repositioning for)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if zone_info["demand_weight"] < 0.05:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         centroid = zone_info["centroid"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Find the fastest available unit that could reach this zone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         best_time = float("inf")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for unit in available_units:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             travel = estimate_travel_time_seconds(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 unit["latitude"], unit["longitude"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 centroid[0], centroid[1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 emergency=True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best_time = min(best_time, travel)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if best_time > COVERAGE_THRESHOLD_SECONDS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             gaps.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "zone_id": zone_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "centroid": centroid,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "best_current_time": round(best_time),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "demand_weight": zone_info["demand_weight"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return gaps
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def optimize_repositioning(fleet, demand_zones):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Solve the repositioning problem: which idle units should move where
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to close coverage gaps?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is formulated as a weighted set-covering assignment problem:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Decision variables: binary (assign unit i to gap j, yes/no)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Objective: minimize total repositioning cost weighted by coverage priority
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Constraints: each gap covered by at most one unit, total moves <= MAX
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Uses OR-Tools' linear solver (SCIP backend) which handles this scale
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (5-50 units, 5-200 zones) in milliseconds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     gaps = identify_coverage_gaps(fleet, demand_zones)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not gaps:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Coverage is adequate. No repositioning needed.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     available_units = [u for u in fleet if u["status"] == "AVAILABLE"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not available_units:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning("No available units for repositioning.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Found %d coverage gaps. %d units available for repositioning.",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 len(gaps), len(available_units))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Create the solver
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     solver = pywraplp.Solver.CreateSolver("SCIP")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not solver:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.error("Could not create SCIP solver. Is OR-Tools installed correctly?")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Decision variables: x[i][j] = 1 if unit i is assigned to cover gap j
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     x = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for i, unit in enumerate(available_units):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for j, gap in enumerate(gaps):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             x[i, j] = solver.IntVar(0, 1, f"x_{i}_{j}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Constraint: each unit can be assigned to at most one gap
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for i in range(len(available_units)):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         solver.Add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             sum(x[i, j] for j in range(len(gaps))) <= 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Constraint: each gap gets at most one unit assigned
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for j in range(len(gaps)):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         solver.Add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             sum(x[i, j] for i in range(len(available_units))) <= 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Constraint: total moves limited
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     solver.Add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sum(x[i, j]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for i in range(len(available_units))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for j in range(len(gaps)))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         <= MAX_REPOSITION_MOVES
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Objective: minimize repositioning cost, weighted by gap priority.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Cost = travel time to reach the gap's centroid.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Priority = demand weight of the uncovered zone (higher demand = more important to cover).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     objective = solver.Objective()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for i, unit in enumerate(available_units):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for j, gap in enumerate(gaps):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             travel = estimate_travel_time_seconds(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 unit["latitude"], unit["longitude"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 gap["centroid"][0], gap["centroid"][1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 emergency=False,  # repositioning is non-emergency driving
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Cost coefficient: travel time penalized, but reduced for high-demand gaps
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # (we're willing to drive farther to cover a high-demand zone)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cost = travel * (1.0 - 0.5 * gap["demand_weight"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             objective.SetCoefficient(x[i, j], cost)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     objective.SetMinimization()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Solve
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     status = solver.Solve()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if status not in (pywraplp.Solver.OPTIMAL, pywraplp.Solver.FEASIBLE):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning("Repositioning solver did not find a feasible solution.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Extract solution: which units move where?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     moves = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for i, unit in enumerate(available_units):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for j, gap in enumerate(gaps):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if x[i, j].solution_value() > 0.5:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 travel = estimate_travel_time_seconds(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     unit["latitude"], unit["longitude"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     gap["centroid"][0], gap["centroid"][1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     emergency=False,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 moves.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "unit_id": unit["unit_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "from_zone": unit["zone"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "to_zone": gap["zone_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "target_position": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "lat": gap["centroid"][0],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "lng": gap["centroid"][1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "repositioning_time_seconds": round(travel),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "gap_demand_weight": gap["demand_weight"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "reason": f"Coverage gap in {gap['zone_id']} "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                               f"(best current response: {gap['best_current_time']}s, "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                               f"threshold: {COVERAGE_THRESHOLD_SECONDS}s)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Repositioning solution: %d moves.", len(moves))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return moves
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 6: Store Dispatch Decision
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Every dispatch decision is written to DynamoDB for the audit trail. In EMS, every decision is reviewable. Medical directors, quality assurance teams, and legal proceedings all need to understand why a particular unit was sent to a particular call.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_dispatch_decision(decision):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write a dispatch decision record to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the audit trail. Every field matters for post-incident review:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Which unit was assigned and why?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - What were the alternatives?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - What was the estimated response time?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - What hospital was recommended?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this table has a TTL for old records (retain 7 years
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     per state EMS record retention requirements) and is encrypted with
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     a KMS CMK.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(DISPATCH_TABLE_NAME)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # DynamoDB requires Decimal for numeric values, not float.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is a known boto3 gotcha that will raise TypeError if you forget.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     record = json.loads(json.dumps(decision), parse_float=Decimal)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Stored dispatch decision: %s", decision.get("call_id", "unknown"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full dispatch pipeline assembled into a single callable function. This is what your Lambda handler would invoke when a 911 call arrives from the CAD system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def dispatch_ambulance(call):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full dispatch optimization for a single incoming call.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         call: dict with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             - call_id: unique identifier from CAD system
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             - location: {lat, lng}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             - priority: 1-5 (1 = life-threatening)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             - required_capability: "ALS" or "BLS"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             - nature_code: e.g., "CHEST_PAIN", "FALL", "MVA"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             - patient_age: (optional) for clinical context
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Complete dispatch decision dict with assigned unit, recommended hospital,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         coverage impact assessment, and all candidates considered.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("DISPATCH REQUEST: %s", call["call_id"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Priority: %d | Nature: %s | Capability: %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 call["priority"], call["nature_code"], call["required_capability"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Location: (%.4f, %.4f)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 call["location"]["lat"], call["location"]["lng"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Load current fleet state (in production: read from DynamoDB)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     fleet = build_initial_fleet()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     demand_zones = build_demand_zones()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Score all available, capable units
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates = score_candidates(call, fleet, demand_zones)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not candidates:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.error("NO AVAILABLE UNITS. Call %s cannot be assigned.", call["call_id"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {"call_id": call["call_id"], "status": "UNASSIGNED", "reason": "no_units"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Best candidate is first in the sorted list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     assigned = candidates[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Assigned: %s (travel: %ds, score: %.4f)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assigned["unit_id"], assigned["travel_time_seconds"], assigned["score"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Select destination hospital based on call nature
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # (In reality, hospital selection happens after on-scene assessment,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # but we compute a preliminary recommendation at dispatch time)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_needs = _infer_patient_needs(call)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hospitals = build_hospital_status()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Use call location as proxy for unit location (unit hasn't arrived yet)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recommended_hospital = select_hospital(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_needs, call["location"], hospitals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if recommended_hospital:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("  Hospital: %s (transport: %.1f min, capacity: %d%%)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     recommended_hospital["name"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     recommended_hospital["transport_time_minutes"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     int(recommended_hospital["capacity_ratio"] * 100))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    779[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    780[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the complete dispatch decision record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     decision = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "call_id": call["call_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "call_priority": call["priority"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "call_location": call["location"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "nature_code": call["nature_code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "assigned_unit": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "unit_id": assigned["unit_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capability": assigned["capability"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "estimated_response_time_seconds": assigned["travel_time_seconds"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "recommended_hospital": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    792[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "hospital_id": recommended_hospital["hospital_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    793[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "name": recommended_hospital["name"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    794[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "transport_time_minutes": recommended_hospital["transport_time_minutes"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    795[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "capacity_ratio": recommended_hospital["capacity_ratio"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    796[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         } if recommended_hospital else None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    797[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "coverage_impact": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    798[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "assigned_unit_impact": assigned["coverage_impact"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    799[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "backup_available": assigned["coverage_impact"] < 0.5,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    800[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    801[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "candidates_evaluated": len(candidates),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    802[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "all_candidates": candidates[:5],  # top 5 for audit trail
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    803[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "decision_timestamp": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    804[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "target_response_time_seconds": RESPONSE_TIME_TARGETS[call["priority"]],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    805[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "meets_target": (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    806[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             assigned["travel_time_seconds"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    807[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             <= RESPONSE_TIME_TARGETS[call["priority"]]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    808[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    809[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    810[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    811[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Meets target: %s (%ds vs %ds threshold)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    812[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 decision["meets_target"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    813[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assigned["travel_time_seconds"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    814[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 RESPONSE_TIME_TARGETS[call["priority"]])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    815[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    816[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    817[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return decision
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    818[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    819[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    820[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _infer_patient_needs(call):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    821[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    822[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Map call nature codes to hospital capability requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    823[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this mapping comes from medical direction protocols
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    824[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and is maintained by the EMS medical director.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    825[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    826[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     nature_to_capabilities = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    827[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "CHEST_PAIN": {"required_capabilities": ["cath_lab"], "acuity_level": 1},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    828[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "STEMI": {"required_capabilities": ["cath_lab", "interventional_cardiology"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    829[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   "acuity_level": 1},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    830[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "STROKE": {"required_capabilities": ["stroke_center"], "acuity_level": 1},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    831[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "TRAUMA_MAJOR": {"required_capabilities": ["level_1_trauma"], "acuity_level": 1},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    832[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "FALL": {"required_capabilities": [], "acuity_level": 3},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    833[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "MVA": {"required_capabilities": ["general_surgery"], "acuity_level": 2},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    834[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "DIFFICULTY_BREATHING": {"required_capabilities": [], "acuity_level": 2},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    835[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    836[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return nature_to_capabilities.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    837[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         call["nature_code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    838[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {"required_capabilities": [], "acuity_level": 3},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    839[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    840[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    841[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    842[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Run the full example ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    843[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if __name__ == "__main__":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    844[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Simulate an incoming Priority 1 cardiac call
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    845[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     incoming_call = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    846[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "call_id": "CAD-2026-0601-1847",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    847[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "location": {"lat": 38.9100, "lng": -77.0350},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    848[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "priority": 1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    849[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "required_capability": "ALS",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    850[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "nature_code": "CHEST_PAIN",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    851[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_age": 67,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    852[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    853[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    854[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Run dispatch optimization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    855[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     decision = dispatch_ambulance(incoming_call)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    856[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("\n--- DISPATCH DECISION ---")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    857[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(json.dumps(decision, indent=2, default=str))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    858[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    859[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Run background repositioning optimization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    860[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("\n--- REPOSITIONING OPTIMIZATION ---")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    861[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     fleet = build_initial_fleet()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    862[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     demand_zones = build_demand_zones()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    863[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     moves = optimize_repositioning(fleet, demand_zones)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    864[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for move in moves:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    865[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"  MOVE: {move['unit_id']} -> {move['to_zone']} "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    866[0m:[38;5;10m[49m               f"({move['repositioning_time_seconds']}s) | {move['reason']}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    867[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not moves:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    868[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print("  No repositioning needed. Coverage is adequate.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    869[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    870[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    871[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    872[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    873[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## The Gap Between This and Production
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    874[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    875[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This example works. Run it and you'll get a scored dispatch decision and repositioning recommendations. But there's a meaningful distance between "works in a script" and "handles real 911 calls." Here's where that gap lives:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    876[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    877[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Real travel times.** The Haversine approximation is wildly inaccurate for urban routing. A point 1 km away across a river with no bridge might be 15 minutes by road. Production requires Amazon Location Service (or equivalent) with real-time traffic data. You'd call `calculate_route_matrix` to get many-to-many travel times for all candidate units simultaneously, then cache results in ElastiCache with a 2-3 minute TTL.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    878[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    879[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **GPS streaming pipeline.** This example uses static fleet positions. Production ingests GPS updates every 5-15 seconds from every unit via Kinesis Data Streams. A Lambda consumer updates DynamoDB on each fix. You need conditional writes (only accept newer timestamps) to handle out-of-order delivery, and you need to detect GPS staleness (unit hasn't reported in 60 seconds = position is unreliable).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    880[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    881[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Demand forecasting.** The static demand weights here are a placeholder. Production trains a time-series model on historical call data (time of day, day of week, weather, events) and hosts it on a SageMaker endpoint. The repositioning optimizer queries this model every cycle to get current demand predictions. Even a simple model (gradient-boosted trees on temporal features) dramatically outperforms static weights.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    882[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    883[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Hospital status integration.** Hospital diversion status, ED census, and bed availability change constantly. Production subscribes to hospital system feeds (HL7 ADT messages, proprietary APIs, or even manual updates from hospital liaisons) via EventBridge. The hospital status table in DynamoDB must have a "last updated" timestamp so you can detect stale data and fall back to conservative assumptions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    884[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    885[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **CAD system integration.** The dispatch decision needs to flow back to the Computer-Aided Dispatch system that dispatchers use. This is typically a proprietary system (Tyler New World, Hexagon, Motorola PremierOne) with its own API or HL7 interface. Integration testing with the CAD vendor is a multi-month effort.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    886[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    887[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Latency budget.** A Priority 1 dispatch must complete in under 2 seconds end-to-end. That means: API Gateway receives the request (50ms), Lambda cold start (eliminated with provisioned concurrency), DynamoDB reads (single-digit ms), travel time lookups (cache hit: 1ms, cache miss with Location Service: 200-500ms), scoring computation (10-50ms), DynamoDB write (single-digit ms). Every millisecond matters. Profile relentlessly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    888[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    889[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Error handling and fallback.** If the Location Service is down, fall back to cached travel times (even if stale). If DynamoDB is unreachable, fall back to an in-memory snapshot. If the scoring function throws an exception, fall back to pure proximity dispatch. The system must always produce an answer. "Sorry, the optimizer crashed" is not acceptable when someone is having a heart attack.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    890[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    891[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Simulation and backtesting.** Before deploying any change to the scoring weights or coverage model, replay 6 months of historical calls through the new logic and compare response time distributions against the old logic. Build a discrete-event simulator that models unit state transitions, travel times, on-scene times, and hospital turnaround times. This is your safety net.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    892[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    893[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Dispatcher override tracking.** Dispatchers will (and should) override the system's recommendations. Track every override: which unit was recommended, which was actually sent, and why. This data is gold for improving the model. If dispatchers consistently override in a specific scenario, the model is missing something.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    894[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    895[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-casualty incident (MCI) mode.** The optimization model assumes independent, sequential calls. An MCI (bus crash, building collapse) generates 5-20 simultaneous patients and requires a completely different allocation strategy. Production needs an MCI detection trigger that switches the system from normal optimization to MCI protocols (triage-based allocation, staging areas, transport coordination).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    896[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    897[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Audit and compliance.** Every dispatch decision is a medical record. Retain for 7+ years per state EMS regulations. Encrypt at rest with KMS CMK. Enable CloudTrail for all API calls. The DynamoDB table needs point-in-time recovery enabled. Consider DynamoDB export to S3 for long-term archival.
